<br>
it can't be done <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
the only way that you can do something similar is to reduce tha ammount of key presses, using social macroes<br>
<br>
this works off the abilities - and for this tutorial, we will use sense heading<br>
<br>
let us assume that sense heading is in the first ability spot - the abilities are numbered - like this:<br>
<br>
12<br>
34<br>
56<br>
<br>
now, as with most abilities, SH is time restricted - it can only be pressed every 21 ticks, or 2.1 seconds<br>
<br>
so, start a new social, call it sense<br>
<br>
the first line should read:<br>
<br>
/pause21,/doability 1<br>
<br>
this makes the computer wait 21 ticks, then does ability number one<br>
<br>
so - fill up the whole of the social box with:<br>
<br>
/pause21,/doability 1<br>
/pause21,/doability 1<br>
/pause21,/doability 1<br>
/pause21,/doability 1<br>
/doability 1<br>
<br>
what this does is every 21 ticks, the senseheading ability is used. (the idea being that five times more likely to get a reading, and increased chance of skill up for each key press)<br>
<br>
so - you will have to sit down with a stop watch and count how long the gap is between kicks.... then change the 21 line above appropriatly....<br>
<br>
<br>
