<br>
One thing to keep in mind is that with the new UI, you don't actually need to use the &quot;social&quot; hotbuttons any more.  You can simply type in /hotbutton  to create a new hotbutton - you can do this to create as many hotbuttons as you want without overwriting any of your socials.<br>
<br>
Another thing that I do that works really well for me is having my &quot;Do Ability&quot; hot button bound to one of my movement keys (I use turn right).  This way, when I'm moving around, I'm actually practicing all four of the skills I listed above at the same time.  If you go into the Options and then Keyboard (I think?), you should be able to select &quot;Macro&quot; from the drop-down list.  This is where your hotbuttons are bound to the various number keys.  At this point, you can make an alternate key for whatever hotbutton you want.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
I use the asdw keys for movement 'cos I'm a FPS junkie. =)  That means that the D key is my right turn key.  I have the second hotbutton set up to do all my abilities, so I find the entry for Hotkey 2 (or whatever it is, I can't remember for sure) and I make the D key the alternate.  That way, when I hit the D key, I both turn right as well as do all my abilities.<br>
<br>
Another tricky thing bards can do is set up a hotbutton that runs a twist for them automatically.  The commands you need to know are /cast , /pause , and /stopsong.  It takes a little experimenting to get the timing down right depending on how many songs you want to twist, but I've had pretty good luck with two-song twists for downtime (mana and healing).  The downside to using hotbuttons is that you have to wait for the whole hotbutton to finish before you can start it up again, even if you miss a note.  So use it carefully. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Mudwayne Theufortew * Level 34 Half Elf Bard</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
